<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED REVIEWS FOR STANLEY CROUCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stanley Crouch's singular goal appears to be to perform some sort of a 
sadomasochistic ritual on the black race, in particular black literary figures 
("Crouch to the Contrary," May 21). 
</P>
<P>
Nothing is cheaper than an analysis of a problem with no problem- solving plan 
of action behind it. Crouch's observations have degenerated to so much 
gibberish, given the absence of any solutions. Rather than offering solutions, 
he is spewing a form of literary cancer exactly like the forms he attacks -- 
i.e., works emasculating the black male. 
</P>
<P>
MARGIE FAIR 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
