<P>
SERIES OF EMERGENCY SUPPLY CENTERS AT SCHOOLS UNVEILED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Because Santa Fe Springs wants its residents to know where to go and what to do 
in an emergency, the city held a public unveiling of its new emergency 
preparedness centers Wednesday morning. 
</P>
<P>
The centers, such as the one officials displayed at Lake Center Junior High 
School, are housed in each of the city's public and private schools and consist 
of a cache containing 72 hours worth of emergency supplies. 
