<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: BELLFLOWER; 
</P>
<P>
DEPUTY MANAGER RESIGNS FOR HAWAIIAN GARDENS JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bellflower Deputy City Administrator Nelson Oliva is resigning to become the 
assistant city administrator of Hawaiian Gardens. 
</P>
<P>
Oliva, 35, began working at Bellflower City Hall in 1980 as a part-time 
recreation leader. In 1985, he became a full-time employee and was rapidly 
promoted. In 1988, Oliva was made deputy city administrator in charge of public 
works and community development. 
</P>
<P>
He said it is difficult for him to leave his fellow employees, but said it was 
time to try "something new and different." His resignation takes effect Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
