BEIJING FREES 97 MORE PROTESTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China freed 97 people jailed for their part in last year's pro-democracy 
demonstrations in a move foreign diplomats said was designed to improve the 
sagging image of Beijing's Communist rulers. The amnesty was announced two days 
after the anniversary of last June's bloody crackdown. 
