<TEXT>
<P>
President Hashemi Rafsanjani urged the United States to press Israel and Kuwait 
to release Muslim prisoners in exchange for help in gaining freedom for Western 
hostages in Lebanon. Iran and the pro-Iranian captors have often demanded that 
Israel free about 350 Muslim prisoners. But it was the first time in months 
that an Iranian leader referred to 15 Shiite Muslims jailed in Kuwait since 
1984 for fatal car bombings. 
