<P>
LUTHERAN CHURCH BURGLARIZED AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time in less than two months, burglars broke into First Lutheran 
Church of Camarillo and stole electronic equipment. 
</P>
<P>
The latest burglary was discovered about 6:30 a.m. Wednesday, according to a 
spokesman for the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. The thieves smashed a 
window to enter the church at 380 Arneill Road during the night. Electronic 
equipment worth about $200 was missing. 
</P>
<P>
About 1 1/2 months ago, a videocassette recorder was taken, a church employee 
said. 
</P>
