<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: NEVER SAW MOLESTATIONS, EX-MCMARTIN TEACHER 
SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former teacher at the McMartin Pre-School who was once a defendant in the 
molestation case testified Wednesday at Ray Buckey's retrial that she never saw 
any molestations occur there. 
</P>
<P>
Babette Spitler was one of seven original defendants when the case was filed in 
1984. 
</P>
<P>
She and four other defendants were dismissed from the case in 1986 because of 
insufficient evidence. 
</P>
<P>
Spitler, testifying on the second day of the defense's case, said she never saw 
any children being molested at the Manhattan Beach preschool. 
</P>
<P>
She testified at the retrial of Buckey, the sole defendant remaining in the 
case. Buckey, 32, is being retried on eight molestation counts alleging that he 
sexually abused three girls at the nursery from 1978 until 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Buckey and his mother, Peggy McMartin Buckey, 63, were acquitted in January of 
52 other molestation counts at the first trial in the case. Jurors deadlocked 
on the eight counts on which Buckey is being retried. 
</P>
</TEXT>
