<HEADLINE>
<P>
PICK OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Antique and rare photography artifacts will be featured at the Western 
Photographic Collectors Show at the Pasadena Center, 300 E. Green St., Saturday 
from 10:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. and Sunday from 10:30 a.m. to 3 p.m. Tickets are $4. 
</P>
<P>
Among the items are a rare poster, above, advertising the first Brownie camera, 
introduced by Kodak in 1900 and sold for $1; the original Kodak camera produced 
in 1888; an 1890 series of box cameras made of polished wood and meant for use 
by children, and a folding camera introduced in 1890. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Eastman Kodak poster 
</P>
