<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: JACKSON DIAGNOSED WITH RIB CAGE 
INFLAMMATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ailing superstar Michael Jackson is suffering from an inflammation of the rib 
cage, but was expected to be released from the hospital within two days to 
continue his recovery at home, his publicist said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Grammy-winning singer underwent extensive testing at St. John's 
Hospital and Health Center in Santa Monica after entering the emergency room 
Sunday with chest pains. 
</P>
<P>
Bob Jones, spokesman for the singer, said Jackson was diagnosed as having 
costochondritis, a condition that results in cartilage inflammation of the 
front part of the ribs. It can be caused by overexertion and stress, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson should be back to work within seven to 10 days, Jones said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Portion of card singer's fans have put in shape of a huge "M" on 
hospital's lawn. RICK MEYER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
