<LENGTH>
<P>
168 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FORM SHOWS MENENDEZES' FRIEND BOUGHT 
SHOTGUNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two days before the savage slayings of entertainment executive Jose Menendez 
and his wife, Kitty, last August in Beverly Hills, two shotguns were purchased 
from a San Diego sporting goods store by a young man who identified himself as 
Donovan Jay Goodreau, a former Princeton roommate of the victims' son, Lyle. 
</P>
<P>
According to a federal firearms transaction form released Wednesday, a person 
identifying himself as Goodreau paid cash for two 12-gauge Mossbergs, costing 
$213.99 each, at a Big 5 store Aug. 18. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities say this type of gun was used in the killings Aug. 20, but the 
murder weapons have not been found. 
</P>
<P>
Lawyers for Lyle Menendez and his brother, Erik, who are charged with the 
murders, had tried to block the document's release. Authorities are still 
seeking to identify the signature on the form. 
</P>
<P>
Goodreau, who could not be reached for comment, reportedly maintains that his 
driver's license -- used for identification -- was stolen and that he was not 
in California at the time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
