<TEXT>
<P>
Texas Air Changing Name: Seven weeks after losing control of Eastern Airlines, 
Texas Air Corp. Chairman Frank Lorenzo said the company would rename itself 
Continental Airlines Holdings Inc. after its main subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
"The name change was made to reflect the fact that the principal business of 
the company is Continental," Lorenzo told shareholders at the company's annual 
meeting. He told reporters later that the change doesn't mean Texas Air has 
given up completely on Eastern, but he declined to comment when asked whether 
he believed he would regain control of the carrier. The name change takes 
effect Monday. 
</P>
