<P>
TURNOUT: The county registrar of voters expected a 50% turnout but got only 
38.2% Tuesday -- putting Orange County 50th among the state's 58 counties. . . 
. Other Southern California counties did even worse: San Diego was 54th; 
Riverside, 55th; Los Angeles, 57th, and San Bernardino dead last. 
