<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST KILLED AFTER HE HITS PICKUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorcyclist who was not wearing a helmet died Tuesday night after crashing 
into a pickup truck which was turning left, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel Aguayo Ponce, 21, of Anaheim was speeding southbound on East Street 
about 8:16 p.m. when he failed to notice that a northbound Mitsubishi pickup 
truck was turning left onto West Wilhelmina Street, Police Lt. Robert Welch 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Ponce was thrown about 100 feet, Welch said, and landed on his head. He was 
dead on arrival at UCI Medical Center in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
No citation was issued to the driver of the pickup. 
</P>
