DRIVER WHO KILLED WOMAN IS SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol is seeking the public's help in finding a 
hit-and-run driver who struck and killed a 78-year-old Laguna Hills woman. 
</P>
<P>
Kathryn Stewart was hit by a small- to mid-size white sedan Saturday as she 
crossed the eastbound lanes of Santa Maria Avenue at Via Vista, CHP spokesman 
Gary Alfonzo said. 
</P>
