<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLASSMAN NAMED TO REPLACE ROSS AS BASEBALL COACH AT SANTA ANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Glassman, who coached 11 years at Willard Intermediate School in Santa Ana, 
has been named to replace Bill Ross as baseball coach at Santa Ana High School. 
</P>
<P>
Glassman, 43, was Ross' assistant this season while continuing as athletic 
director at Willard. 
</P>
<P>
He also was an assistant for two years under Herschel Musick at Santa Ana 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Ross, the dean of the county's baseball coaches, resigned following the 1990 
season. He had a 477-235 record in 32 seasons and led Santa Ana to the 1982 
Southern Section 3-A division title. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a unique situation to replace a man who was a legend in his own time," 
Glassman said. "I learned a lot from Bill this year as his assistant, and it 
will be a challenge replacing him. 
</P>
<P>
"It will be an exciting challenge to move into the Sunset League next season, 
and I'm looking forward to playing in the best baseball league in the county." 
</P>
<P>
Glassman developed some top players who went to Santa Ana, including Julio 
Vargas, Robbie Johnson, Bob Reimers, Hector Olivares and John Schilling. 
</P>
<P>
Olivares will be Glassman's assistant and Schilling will remain as the school's 
pitching coach. 
</P>
<P>
Glassman will remain as athletic director at Willard. Ross will stay at Santa 
Ana as athletic director. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment 
</P>
</TYPE>
