O.C. BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Afcom Seeks Protection: Afcom, which once ranked among the 100 largest home 
builders in California, has filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. 
</P>
<P>
The Sunset Beach firm listed total assets of $500 and total liabilities of 
$89,581 though it said it owed a related company, Sonju Construction, more than 
$800,000. Sonia Sonju, a former Cypress councilwoman, is listed as Afcom's 
president in the filing. She was not available for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
