<P>
WORKER ON DRILL RIG ELECTROCUTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man working on a drilling rig near Palmdale died of electric shock after 
equipment he was operating struck a power line, Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputies said today. 
</P>
<P>
Scott Rounds, 24, of Oxnard died at Palmdale Hospital Medical Center about 4 
p.m. Wednesday. He had been taken there by a co-worker after a drilling rig he 
was operating struck and knocked down a power line in a field near Elizabeth 
Lake Road and Bouquet Canyon in Leona Valley, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Rounds was working for Buena Engineering of Lancaster and was drilling soil 
test holes when the accident occurred about 3:30 p.m., deputies said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
